rComments: Passionate Prof. Cares a lot about the topic shes discusses. Just do the readings and go every to lecture and you should do fine. Take lots of notes when she talks.
Different style, says what she feels which takes getting used to, but she's very sincere about helping students learn and bends over backwards for us.

I only PRAY that she did not receive tenurship...she is absolutely terrible!  I busted my butt, for what?...a dinky C+ (what a waste of time, and the person who wrote earliarabout your other courses suffer from the crap she expects!) They were TOTALLY right....just don't take GGR342...I will regret it till my dying day!

She is a nice person to speak with, but as a professor, I really suggest you not take this course....not only did I NOT kill myself to TRY to get a good grade, in the end, I did poorly, and the rest of my courses suffered....don't take this course unless u have nothing better to do!
She was nice as a person, however, her class was disorganized. We didn't get any clear definition of key terms at all. The reading material seemed to be a bit too much for the half-year course.

Absolutely terrible!  Yes she is a nice person, but that doesn't help much when she blantly states that her readings alone will NOT ensure a good mark.  Then why bother putting the readings together at all?...she was very evasive in that sense!
